            article
              p.sans
                strong
                  | When is check-in and check-out?
              p
                | Check-in 4:00 PM: Do not check in at the property unless otherwise directed to do so. Check in at the Océano Rentals office on Fremont Blvd. Directions to the office are above.
              p
                | Check-out 12:00 PM: Please return the key to our office by noon (Arizona time) on your check-out day. Do not leave the key at the unit or at the Guard House. If you leave early, there is a key drop at the office.
            article
              p.sans
                strong
                  | What is the cancellation policy?
              p
                | Cancellations made thirty (30) or more days prior to scheduled arrival will be charged $50 or 20%, of the Booking Deposit whichever is more; for cancellations made twenty-nine (29) to fifteen (15) days prior to scheduled arrival, the Booking Deposit will be forfeited. If cancellation is made in less than fourteen (14) days prior to scheduled arrival, all rental monies and tax, excluding Security Deposit and cleaning fee will be forfeited. No refunds will be given for holiday time periods. Recognized holidays can be found here.
            article
              p.sans
                strong
                  | What is the policy on pets?
              p
                | If a homeowner has specifically requested that renters cannot bring pets, we are obligated to respect that stipulation. Please do not request any alteration to this policy or ignore it in such a way as to risk eviction and no refund of rent or security deposit monies.
              ol
                li
                  | If a pet is found on a property which does not allow pets, the occupants will be evicted immediately with loss of all rental monies, cleaning fee, taxes and security deposit.
                li
                  | If a pet is found on a property which does allow pets, and prior arrangements have not been made with Océano Rentals, the occupants will be evicted immediately with loss of all rental monies, cleaning fee, taxes and security deposit.
            article
              p.sans
                strong
                  | When is the balance due?
              p
                | Balance of Payment Policy: The balance of the rent, tax, cleaning fee and security deposit are due thirty (30) days prior to arrival. The balance payment can be made by check by phone, credit card, check, cashier's check or money order. Please allow 5 days for mailing and send payments to Océano Rentals, P.O. Box 2357, Litchfield Park, AZ 85340, or payments may be made directly to Océano Account #7372-03117 at any Chase/Bank One in the United States. Please fax a copy of the receipt with your name and reservation number to (928) 569-0051. Checks drawn from financial institutions outside the State of Arizona will not be accepted. Reservations will not be held if the booking deposit or balance payments are not received by the respective due dates. A late fee of $10 will be charged for balances paid after the due date. Returned checks will be charged a minimum of $25 fee.
            article
              p.sans
                strong
                  | Does Océano accept personal checks?
              p
                | Yes, Océano accepts Checks by Phone or you can send a personal checks provided that the following criteria are met:
              ol
                li
                  | The check is drawn from a bank in the State of Arizona.
                li
                  | The check is received by the due date or 30 days prior to arrival, whichever is more.
            article
              p.sans
                strong
                  | Does Océano accept credit cards?
              p
                | Océano does accept Visa and MasterCard for payments. The transaction will be in U.S. Dollars.
            article
              p.sans
                strong
                  | When will my deposit be returned?
              p
                | Security deposits will be returned in about two weeks.
            article
              p.sans
                strong
                  | What is I.V.A.?
              p
                | I.V.A. is a Mexican national sales tax. The tax rate in this region of Mexico is 12%.
            article
              p.sans
                strong
                  | Can I bring ATVs, dune buggies, dirt bikes, rails or wave runners?
              p
                | The above are not allowed in Las Conchas and the rules for Las Conchas are below.
              p
                | Important Las Conchas Notice: The Las Conchas Homeowners' Association Rules and our homeowners prohibit renters from bringing in ATVs, dune buggies, dirt bikes, rails or wave runners into the Las Conchas community. Violators, who do so, risk impoundment of the vehicle(s) and prosecution by the local police. These vehicles brought in by renters or visitors, with or without Las Conchas stickers, will be refused entry at the Guard Gate. Violators who bypass the Guard Gate do so at the risk of impoundment of the vehicle(s) and prosecution by the local police. The Association and the city of Puerto Peñasco enacted this ordinance to preserve the desert environment which was rapidly being destroyed by off road vehicles. At no time are any of these vehicles to be ridden on the beach side of Las Conchas (with the exception of the Las Conchas Guards patrolling the area and enforcing the rules).
            article
              p.sans
                strong
                  | Are fireworks allowed?
              p
                | No! Fireworks are illegal in Mexico and not allowed in any of our properties. You are subject to eviction if you use fireworks.
            article
              p.sans
                strong
                  | What are the office hours?
              p
                | Océano Rentals is open everyday from 10:00 AM-5:00 PM and until 7:00 PM on Fridays.
            article
              p.sans
                strong
                  | Should I bring drinking water?
              p
                | We recommend that you either purchase bottled water here in Puerto Peñasco or bring it with you. The bottled water here in Puerto Peñasco has been processed by reverse osmosis (RO). We do not recommend that you drink the water from the faucets.
            article
              p.sans
                strong
                  | Do I need to bring linens or towels?
              p
                | You do not need to bring any bed linens or bath towels. Océano provides bed linens and bath towels for all of our properties. We do ask that you bring your own beach towels and that you do not take the bath towels to the beach.
            article
              p.sans
                strong
                  | Do I need to bring beach towels or chairs?
              p
                | Yes. Please bring your own beach towels and chairs for the beach. These items are not provided. Please do not take the towels provided for bathing nor the patio furniture to the beach.
            article
              p.sans
                strong
                  | What do I need to cross the border?
              p
                | When you cross the border, make sure that you have identification for all passengers and registration for your vehicles.
              p
                | Do not bring rifles, pistols, or ammunition of any kind across the border!
          .g.sm-one-half
            article
              p.sans
