                  | Do I need special car insurance to drive in Mexico?
              p
                | Yes you do. It is very important that each car that crosses into Mexico has proper coverage. Mexican Law is very strict regarding uninsured motorists that get into an accident. To make it as simple as possible for our customers, you can purchase your car insurance online by 
                a[href="http://web2web.mexicoinsuranceonline.com/index.cgi?agentcode=DEKACF"]
                  | clicking here
                | .
            article
              p.sans
                strong
                  | When is the border open?
              p
                | The border is open daily from 6:00 AM to 12:00 AM midnight.
            article
              p.sans
                strong
                  | Can I use my cellular phone in Rocky Point?
              p
                | Rocky Point does have cellular phone technology. Rocky Point has TDMA - digital, CDMA - digital, and analog cellular technologies. Be sure to call your cellular phone provider prior to crossing the border for any specific instructions on using your phone in Mexico.
            article
              p.sans
                strong
                  | How do I use my calling card in Mexico?
              p
                | We recommend that you make contact with your calling card company prior to your vacation to learn the specifics. We have found most of the information for using calling cards on the websites of the respective companies.
              ul
                li
                  | MCI - 
                  a[href="http://consumer.mci.com/international/english/resources/accessnos.jsp"]
                    | Check the complete list of WorldPhone toll-free access numbers
                li
                  | AT&T - 
                  a[href="http://www.business.att.com/default/?pageid=bt_dialing_instr&branchid=bt"]
                    | AT&T Travel Guide
            article
