              p.sans
                strong
                  | Peace of mind damage waiver.
              p
                | Why worry that someone in your party might accidentally break something? Relax and enjoy your stay. If an accident happens, report the details and leave the rest to us. Guest is required to pay a nonrefundable “Peace of Mind Damage Waiver Fee" to cover any unintentional damage to the property, up to ten times said Fee. Damage in excess of this amount or damage that is deemed by Océano Rentals to be of an intentional nature will be charged to Guest's credit card. The damage waiver DOES NOT cover intentional damage, theft, additional cleaning, or pet damage. Guests will report incidents causing damage to the property immediately to our office or call (888) 328 8491 (From the U.S.), (638) 383 0800 (From Mexico).
              p
                | The Staff of Océano Rentals will determine all necessary repairs. Report all damages to Océano rentals by the day of check-out.
              p
                | All guests staying in the property (not to exceed maximum occupancy) will be covered by this waiver and will not be obligated to pay for accidental loss or damage to the rental unit or its contents.
              p
                | The Accidental Damage Waiver does not include:
              ol
                li
                  | Intentional acts, gross negligence or willful conduct
                li
                  | Evidence of and/or damage caused by pets (pets are prohibited in rental properties)
                li
                  | Damage done by unauthorized groups
                li
                  | Loss or damage to guest's personal property or rental equipment brought onto the premises
                li
                  | Normal wear and tear
                li
                  | Damage to electric vehicles (golf carts)
                li
                  | Any damage caused by a violation of Océano Rentals' Rules & Regulations or in an action that violates local, state or federal laws
                li
                  | Acts of nature
            article
