                  | What documents are required to return to the U.S. after visiting Puerto Peñasco (Rocky Point)?
              p
                | Effective January 31, 2008 United States and Canadian citizens 19 years of age and older, returning by land from Mexico will be required to show a government issued I.D. (drivers license) and a copy of their birth certificate. Children 18 and under must present a copy of their birth certificate. This is an interim change that will be in effect until June 2009 when all U.S. citizens will be required to present a valid U.S. Passport for re-entry into the U.S. For more detail on this and other foreign travel related information 
                a[href="http://www.cbp.gov/travel/us-citizens/whti-program-background/docs-land-sea"]
                  | click here
                | .
            article
              p.sans
                strong
                  | What are the best times to return from Puerto Peñasco to avoid long delays at the border check point?
              p
                | Generally weekday traffic returning to Arizona is light to moderate with delays less than 15-20 minutes. Weekend return traffic Sunday (also Monday on 3 day weekends) can be moderate to heavy during peak hours (9:00 AM-5:00 PM) with delays occasionally well over an hour. Traffic wait time estimates are posted and updated hourly 
                a[href="http://bwt.cbp.gov"]
                  | on the internet
                | . Our clients have reported that these wait time estimates have been accurate.
            article
              p.sans
                strong
                  | Where can I get accurate information on the process for getting a U.S. Passport?
              p
                | Passport information and application forms are available 
                a[href="http://www.travel.state.gov/passport/forms/forms_847.html"]
                  | online
                | .
            article
